    <section>
        <title>Build script structure</title>
        <para>A build script is made up of zero or more statements and blocks. Statements can include method calls
            or property assignments. Being a Groovy script, a build script can also contain method and class definitions.
            The blocks are listed below:</para>
        <table>
            <title>Build script blocks</title>
            <tr>
                <td>allprojects</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>artifacts</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>buildscript</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>configurations</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>dependencies</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>repositories</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>subprojects</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </section>

